         <abstract resp="pers:KS1">
            <p>Isn’t it curious that <title level="j">Hearst’s</title> synopsis of the serial novel claims that Marion’s mother is a <q>Frenchwoman</q> while the novel begins with French Montrealers whispering about her foreignness? But perhaps it’s unsurprising; this was the era of the Chinese Exclusion Act and of fierce prejudice against the Chinese! You would never know, reading the fourth instalment, that the passage taken across the border by the <q>real</q> Marion—-Sara Bosse, Winnifred Eaton’s half-Chinese sister—-was fraught with danger, or that her beau’s reluctance to marry her had to do with anything more than her financial status! </p>
         </abstract>
